MILWAUKEE (AP) — The Milwaukee Public Museum will close for several days next week as staffers wait for COVID-19 test results. The Milwaukee Journal Sentinel reported Friday that the museum will be closed Monday through Wednesday. Museum President and CEO Ellen Censky said in a statement that key staff members in essential operational roles are quarantining or waiting for test results.People who bought tickets for the now-closed days can get a refund or transfer their tickets to another date. The museum requires masks for all staff and visitors over age 3. Censky said in her statement that 97% of the museum’s employees are vaccinated and those who aren’t are tested weekly for the disease.